[Handgeschreven kopie] [recto] Ad [Addendum] 19. Woman taken in Adultery. Letter from Alexander Hope, Esq. to Count Seilern, 24 Aug. 1953. Korte inhoud: Herkomst: General Sir Alexander Hope (younger son of the Earl of Hopetoun), Luffness. Acquired at Hampden Sale 1834; [verso] [toegevoegde vermelding] 'F.G. The label on the back of the picture says:"Woman taken in Adultery. By Bruegel. Was in the collection of Viscountess Hampden and left to G.W.H."; Who is G.W. H. (Hope)? Look up Hope in arms...[sic].'[scan]
